### Phase 6: Modify -- `client/src/components/Universe/components/StarGroup.jsx`

**Changes:**

Add drag event handling to the star's core circle. The key challenge is converting Konva drag events (which are in screen/stage space) to world coordinates that the physics engine understands.

```javascript
const StarGroup = React.memo(({ 
    x, y, radius, color, title, showTitle, isPulsing, onClick,
    draggable, onDragStart, onDragMove, onDragEnd 
}) => {
    // ... existing code ...

    // The bright core circle becomes draggable
    <Circle
        radius={r * 0.5}
        fill="#ffffffee"
        shadowColor="#ffffff"
        shadowBlur={4}
        shadowOpacity={1}
        perfectDrawEnabled={false}
        hitStrokeWidth={r + 12}
        onClick={onClick}
        onTap={onClick}
        draggable={draggable}
        onDragStart={(e) => {
            e.cancelBubble = true;  // prevent stage drag
            if (onDragStart) {
                const stage = e.target.getStage();
                const pos = stage.getPointerPosition();
                // Convert screen to world coords (needs camera/zoom context)
                // This conversion will be passed down or computed here
                onDragStart({ x: e.target.getAbsolutePosition().x, y: e.target.getAbsolutePosition().y });
            }
        }}
        onDragMove={(e) => {
            e.cancelBubble = true;
            if (onDragMove) {
                onDragMove({ x: e.target.getAbsolutePosition().x, y: e.target.getAbsolutePosition().y });
            }
        }}
        onDragEnd={(e) => {
            e.cancelBubble = true;
            if (onDragEnd) onDragEnd();
        }}
    />
```

**Important consideration:** Konva's `draggable` on a Konva node will move the Konva node itself. But we want the physics engine to control position. So instead of making the Konva node `draggable`, we should handle raw pointer events and feed them to the physics drag constraint. The Konva node position is then driven by the physics body position on the next frame. This prevents the visual "snap" that would occur with Konva's built-in drag.

**Revised approach:** Instead of Konva `draggable`, use `onMouseDown`/`onTouchStart` on the core circle to initiate the physics drag, and let the existing stage-level `onMouseMove`/`onMouseUp` in `Universe.jsx` route to the physics system when a drag is active. This is cleaner and avoids fighting Konva's drag system.

